<h3>Question 11</h3>
<div><p><p>You have to give a presentation on one of the occasions at college. Write a short speech<br />
on difficulty of being a student and employee.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Ladies and gentlemen,</p>
<p>Today, I want to talk about something that many of us can relate to—the tough time of being<br />
both a student and having a job. I want to discuss the difficulties we face when we try to<br />
balance our studies and work responsibilities. Being a student and an employee at the same<br />
time is not easy. It brings its own set of challenges. Let me explain a few of them in simple<br />
terms:</p>
<p>First, managing our time becomes really hard. We have to find a way to attend classes, study,<br />
do our assignments, and also do our job. It&#8217;s a lot to handle and requires us to plan well and<br />
stay organized. Second, it can make us feel tired and stressed. We have to constantly switch<br />
between being a student and going to work. This can make us feel exhausted and<br />
overwhelmed. We need to take care of ourselves and make sure we have time for rest and<br />
relaxation. Also, our busy schedule can make it difficult for us to be flexible. Sometimes, our<br />
work hours clash with our class schedule, making it hard to attend all our classes or participate in group projects. We have to find a way to balance everything and make compromises.</p>
<p>Money can be a big concern too. Many of us work to earn money for our education and daily<br />
expenses. It can be stressful to manage our work hours and still have time for our studies. We<br />
have to be careful with our finances and make sacrifices sometimes. But despite these<br />
difficulties, being a student and an employee also teaches us important skills. We learn how to<br />
manage our time, handle multiple tasks, and become more responsible. It prepares us for our<br />
future careers and makes us stronger individuals.</p>
<p>In conclusion, being a student and an employee is not easy. It requires hard work, good time<br />
management, and a lot of determination. But with support, understanding, and a positive<br />
attitude, we can overcome these challenges and come out stronger in the end.</p>
<p>Thank you for listening.</p>
</div>
