other grow.</p>
<p>At Shikhar IT Solutions, we believe that learning is a lifelong journey, and we want to create an environment where we can share our skills and experiences to become even better professionals. The &#8220;Shared Experience for Growth&#8221; program is designed to do just that!<br />
Here&#8217;s what you can expect from the program:</p>
<p>&#8211; We&#8217;ll have sessions where you can voluntarily share your skills and expertise with your colleagues. This is a chance to show what you&#8217;re really good at and teach others.<br />
&#8211; The program also offers opportunities for mentorship. You can be a mentor and guide someone who could benefit from your knowledge and experience.<br />
&#8211; We encourage collaboration on projects. By working together, we can learn from each other and come up with innovative ideas.<br />
&#8211; We want to acknowledge your efforts! Outstanding participants will be recognized for their dedication to learning and for helping their colleagues grow.</p>
<p>We&#8217;re excited to see how this program will help us all learn and grow together. If you have any questions or ideas, please reach out to the program coordinators or the HR department. Let&#8217;s make the most of this opportunity and create a supportive and inspiring learning environment at Shikhar IT Solutions!</p>
<p>Best regards,<br />
Ankit Pangeni<br />
Managing Director<br />
Shikhar IT Solution</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 15</h3>
<div><p><p>The Board of Directors of your company Nepal Distillery Ltd. has passed a proposal on providing bonus and incentives to all the employees. As a secretary of the company, you are responsible for informing the staff about the decision taken by the board meeting. Write a memo informing about the recently taken decision.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Nepal Distillert Ltd<br />
MEMORANDUM<br />
To: All Staff<br />
From: Ankit Pangeni<br />
Date: 12th July 2023</p>
<p>Subject: Announcement of Bonus and Incentives</p>
<p>I hope this memo finds you well. I am writing to inform you about an important decision made by the Board of Directors in the recent meeting regarding bonus and incentives for all employees at Nepal Distillery Ltd.</p>
<p>We are pleased to announce that the Board of Directors has passed a proposal to provide bonus and incentives as a token of appreciation for your hard work, dedication, and valuable contributions to the company&#8217;s success. This decision reflects the company&#8217;s commitment to recognizing and rewarding the efforts of our exceptional staff members.</p>
<p>All eligible employees will receive a bonus based on their individual performance during a specific time period. The Human Resources department will share more information about how your performance will be evaluated and how the bonus will be calculated. We will also introduce an incentive program to reward exceptional achievements, innovative ideas, and outstanding performance. The details about who is eligible, how to participate, and how winners will be chosen will be provided to you soon. The Board of Directors wants to express<br />
their gratitude for your hard work and dedication. Please keep up the great work and continue to show your dedication in your roles. Your contributions are highly valued and make a difference at Nepal Distillery Ltd.</p>
<p>If you have any questions or need more information about this exciting announcement, please reach out to the Human Resources department. Once again, congratulations to all employees on this well-deserved recognition and appreciation.</p>
<p>Thank you.<br />
Sincerely,<br />
Ankit Pangeni<br />
Secretary<br />
Nepal Distillery Ltd</p>
